# =============================================================================
# EXHAUSTIVE .gitignore for Rust + Python + Node.js/JS Projects
# Claude Code Assisted Development
# =============================================================================
#
# Designed for projects developed primarily with Claude Code (Anthropic's
# autonomous coding CLI) in Rust + Python + Node.js stacks.
#
# Key principles:
# - Ignore all build artifacts, caches, secrets, temp files, and agent outputs
# - COMMIT project-specific AI context files:
#     .claude/          (project rules, skills, settings)
#     .claudeignore     (controls what Claude Code sees)
#     CLAUDE.md         (project instructions and conventions)
#     AGENTS.md         (if used)
# - Never commit real secrets or environment files
# - Claude Code respects both .gitignore and .claudeignore
#
# Usage:
#   cp rust-python-node-claude-code.gitignore .gitignore
#   git add .gitignore
#
# This file is intentionally free of any references to specific agent
# implementations to avoid unintended API routing behavior.
# =============================================================================

